1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nd5 Be7 {A very logical move. Black focuses on quick development. The bishop's position is perhaps not impressive, but it does prevent Bg5 ideas.} 6. Bc4 {Other moves are certainly possible but this one appeals to me the most. What's more, Black is tempted to take the pawn on e4 , which leads to some spicy chess.} Nxe4 7. O-O {For a split second Black has coordination issues. The knight on e4 as well as the king on e8 mean a chance for creating tactical motifs along the e file. Black needs to castle as quickly as possible and retreat the knight. In the meantime, White will attempt to develop a powerful initative.} Nd6 {This seemingly normal move allows a nice tactical trick.} 8. Bf4 Nxc4 {Black can't take the bishop as it drops the queen.} 9. Bxc7 {The queen is trapped. Yay!} *


