1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nd5 d6 {An extremely rare continuation (not only at the high level). Such a move is most likely to be played by someone surprised by the Belgrade Gambit and trying to avoid your opening preparation.   Nice try! Luckily, we anticipated that as well.} 6. Nxd4 ({Simple and efficient. Obviously, centralization of the next minor piece is very beneficial, but it is also important to keep in mind that the e4 pawn might be hanging in some lines. As a matter of fact, White already indirectly protects the e4 pawn, as taking it would lead to a completely lost position for Black. Now we will cover as many as five options for Black: A1: Nxe4 , A2: Nxd5 , A3: Bd7 , A4: Bg4 , A5:} 6. Nxd4 {and A6:} Be7 {.}) 6... Be7 7. Bb5 Bd7 {Surprisingly, this is a very important position. So far, White has obtained a promising edge, but it's somewhat elusive. It's critical to understand that Black threatens massive exchanges of minor pieces and when that happens, Black's problems will be over.} 8. Nf5 {This is an attempt to make things spicy and imbalanced. Black has a chance to take the knight and worsen White's pawn structure. In return, White gets the bishop pair and a strange type of a pawn majority on kingside.} (8. O-O $6 {positionally, this is dubious as it allows massive simplifications.} Nxd5 9. exd5 Nxd4 10. Bxd7+ Qxd7 11. Qxd4 O-O {Black is certainly not worse. It's a type of position we want to avoid at any cost. Simple, dull, yuck!}) 8... O-O {Gives White a pleasant edge for free.} 9. Nfxe7+ Nxe7 10. Nxf6+ gxf6 11. Bd3 {One of the keys to a successful attack: it is vital to keep as many pieces on the board as possible. Imagine the b1 - h7 diagonal opening for the bishop and the queen joining the attack via h5 . Wonderful, isn't it?} Ng6 12. Bh6 Re8 13. O-O Ne5 14. Qh5 {White's opening has been a tremendous success. The bishop pair combined with a better pawn structure and Black's dubious king safety give White a solid plus. The Black king is an obvious target. The possible continuation is f2 - f4 followed by Rf3 - g3 .} *

