1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nd5 Bc5 {It's a very important line. To my surprise, it is not employed frequently. Black provokes 6.Bg5 with a pin. The problem is that Black will then retreat to e7 with the bishop and White pretty much has to go back to f4 . As a result, we have a 5... Be7 6.Bf4 line with both sides losing a tempo. However, I never intended to recommend 6. Bf4 against the Be7 system. Therefore, my main remedy against Bc5 system will be a bit different.} 6. Bf4 d6 7. Bg5 {The bishop keeps on dancing! You shouldn't make multiple moves in the opening with the same piece unless the author of the course tells you to do so. Here, you have my blessing to create the pin along the h4 - d8 diagonal. As usual, this means paralysing Black's forces to a degree. It will be impossible to take on e4 or d5 , which is already something to cherish.} Be6 8. Bb5 {Thanks to the pin along a4 - e8 diagonal, White threatens to win the d pawn.} a6 9. Bxc6+ bxc6 10. Nxf6+ gxf6 11. Bh4 {The position is very complex. To an untrained eye, it seems that Black is in a very bad shape here. After all, he has 2 sets of doubled pawns and may lose the d4 pawn soon. On top of that, there is the exposed king on e8 , which has no place to go. Still, Black has a bishop pair and a move!} Bb4+ {Most likely the strongest continuation. Otherwise, White castles with a comfortable game.} 12. Nd2 Rg8 13. O-O c5 14. Nb3 {It's evident that the bishop on b4 is out of play. White has a few interesting ideas from here: Qh5 , Qf3 , f4 or a3 .} Qd7 {Black's best try is to abandon the f6 pawn and aim for counterplay with Bh3 as soon as White captures on f6 .} 15. f3 {White needs to strengthen the position before playing anything active. Now Rf2 will be a good defensive resource. It's still unclear what Black should do with his king and this is certainly good news. The position is complex and all results are possible.} (15. Bxf6 $4 {It's a trap! White really shouldn't be so greedy here. The bishop is the only piece, which can properly defend the White king. Having the possibility of retreating it to g3 is a critical resource.} Bh3 {We really don't want this to happen. White will lose material.}) *


