 Qxe7 9. Bd3 {Black has numerous options here so I took the liberty of analyzing only the most critical lines. I believe you should be able to handle the rest with logical moves.} d5 {The most forcing and probably tempting for Black as the e4 pawn is pinned.} 10. Bg5 {Clearly the strongest. We need to develop the pieces fast and this helps to deal with Black's idea by liquidating into a much better endgame. I also tested 10.e5 but the results were really bad. So bad that I will not even share them.} dxe4 11. Bxf6 Qxf6 12. Qxf6 gxf6 13. Bxe4 {I know it will be difficult to win a quick game from this position but Black will really face a difficult defensive task due to much worse pawn structure, a passive bishop and a king stuck in the centre of the board. Your next moves should probably be O-O-O followed by Rhe1 .} *

