ial activity along a1 - h8 diagonal. Later, White may also attempt to reposition the bishop to c2 and use it to attack along the b1 - h7 diagonal, possibly with the queen on d3 .} a6 13. Ba4 Bf6 {White is obliged to attack or else he will lose the momentum.} 14. g4 {The pawn avalanche should not be underestimated. White threatens to play g4 - g5 .} (14. Bd2 $6 {I don't see how the bishop is better on d2 as compared to c1 .} b5 15. Bc2 Ne5 16. Rae1 Rfe8 17. Bc1 c6 18. Qd1 d5 19. Re2 {White didn't achieve enough activity for the compromised pawn structure.}) 14... h6 {This simply creates a pawn hook in Black's position. As soon as White manages to reinforce g4 - g5 with f2 - f4 , further march of the pawns will be deadly!} 15. f4 {With g5 coming and Black is about to be demolished.} *

