 pawns.} 12. Qb3 (12. Qxb7 $4 {Please kindly do not fall for this (unless you really like blundering pieces).} Rb8 13. Qf3 Rxb5 {Black has a decisive advantage.}) 12... Nc6 13. c3 {Avoiding Nd4 ideas.} Bf6 14. Qd5 {White threatens to take on c6 . An additional interesting idea might be to play f4 and g4 with an attack on kingside and extra control over e5 square.} *

