y the d , e and possibly f pawns combined.   White's next moves should definitely be aggressive: b4 , a4 with a pawn avalanche on the queenside.   It seems that Black may need a few preparatory moves to start his own pawn roll on the kingside. I like White's chances, but it may be more difficult than expected in reality.} *

