3 .} a5 {Not forced, but Black should try to play on the queenside. The pawn on a7 could have turned out to be a tactical liability in certain lines.} 15. f3 Ng5 16. Qc3 {White's setup is much more logical. The queen puts pressure on a5 and c6 . In the long run, the plan is typical for such types of positions: full throttle on the kingside (I'm talking about advancing the pawns to avoid any confusion)!} *

