1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nd5 h6 {This move actually makes some sense. Black is simply trying to prevent 6.Bg5 with the irritating pin. Yet, it is a rather rare choice for Black - at least at a higher level.   The great majority of this chapter originates from computer analysis. Still, it's worth learning these lines as they nicely present certain ideas, which we will use in other positions.   I don't recommend memorizing all of it. Try to treat this chapter as a unique chance to increase your resourcefulness.   When preparing this chapter, I didn't expect to find so many fascinating tactical and strategic ideas. Welcome to the Belgrade jungle!} 6. Bf4 {White develops the bishop, attacking the c7 pawn and threatening to score the point.} Nxd5 {This move could be treated as the mainline of 5... h6 . From Black's perspective, it makes a lot of sense to take on d5 in order to develop the bishop to b4 and, later on, the queen to e7 . A very tempting continuation.} 7. exd5 Qf6 8. Bd2 {It is necessary to bring the bishop back. Fortunately, Black still needs to find a good square for the knight.} Ne7 9. Bc4 b6 10. O-O Bb7 {It's one of those positions in the course, which made me realize I may not have all of the answers. Playing positions with a pawn deficit is good provided that White has realistic chances for initiative. This time, it will not be so easy.} 11. c3 {As usual, every single piece has to be involved, so we're trying to provoke Black to take on c3 .} Nxd5 12. Re1+ Be7 13. cxd4 O-O 14. Qb3 {The compensation for the pawn is not clear here. Thanks to the pressure along a2 - g8 diagonal, Black has realistic tactical problems as the knight lacks sufficient support. Is this enough, though? I only know that it looks easier to play for White.} Qd6 15. Re5 c6 16. Rae1 Bf6 17. Rh5 Rfe8 18. Ne5 {Black has to be really careful not to blunder anything here. True to this opening's style, we may even consider something as brave as f4 - g4 - g5 . According to the engine, White has microscopically better chances.} *

