ly, this just doesn't work.} Rh8 {White's bishops are in jeopardy.} 12. Qd3 Nb4 {White cannot protect the bishop.}) 11... Be6 12. Bb5 Bd6 13. Bg3 {Exchanging is fine, but on our terms! If Black takes on g3 , after the correct recapture with the h pawn, White's rook will be very active. White is about to win the d pawn, which will give him a tremendous compensation for the pawn. Your next move will most likely be Nxd4 or Bxc6 followed by Nxd4 .} *

