Once you understand what Black hoped to do, it becomes evident that White needs to do something on queenside. In fact, we're also looking for b4 - b5 ideas to drive the Black knight to a less active position.} O-O {Allowing b4 - b5 is not a good idea. White gets insant initiative.} 12. b5 Na5 {At this point, Black should have given a pawn back. The following line is both illustrative and impressive.} 13. Nxd4 {First punch! The knight is pinned and it really shouldn't leave its defensive post.} Nxd4 14. Nxe7+ Kh8 15. Qh5 {White's attack is powerful. In fact, the engine already claims that Black is lost, perhaps due to the Bf4 - Bxh6 idea with checkmate to follow. Another idea is a simple Bh4 with numerous threats on kingside  (such as Ng6 +).} *

