1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nd5 Nb4 {One of the mainlines in the Belgrade Gambit. Black attempts to exchange our mighty knight on d5 without losing a tempo (which was the case after the immediate 5... Nxd5 ). In fact, the knight is attacked twice, which forces a reaction.} 6. Bc4 (6. Qxd4 $4 Nxc2+ {Say goodbye to your queen.}) 6... Nbxd5 7. exd5 {We have reached a very important branching point, so please make sure to study White's reactions properly.} Bc5 {The position is almost symmetric, but the d4 pawn is already attacked and the bishop on c1 is about to be activated. Ironically, there will be positions, when taking on d4 will not be advisable as it will only increase the scope of the Black bishop on c5 .} 8. O-O O-O 9. Bg5 d6 10. h3 {The d4 pawn will not escape and it's worth playing a few prophylactic moves. First of all, the Black bishop is not to be allowed on g4 .} Re8 11. Bd3 {I like this subtle multipurpose move. The bishop on c8 is deprived of the f5 square, so its options are limited with every single move. More importantly, White's light-square bishop is not restricted by the d5 anymore. The plan is simple: Qd2 followed by Qf4 with pressure on f6 and d4 .} h6 12. Bh4 g5 {Definitely one of the critical continuations. If this works, Black may have a reasonable position.} 13. Nxg5 {We need to go all in. From a strategic perspective, the sacrifice is justified as the Black's bishops are out of play and so is the rook on a8 . Handling the pin along h4 - d8 diagonal will not be easy for Black, either.} hxg5 14. Bxg5 {White threatens Qf3 with a powerful attack.} Re5 {Black needs to react as quickly as possible as there is no tomorrow if White includes the queen in the attack.} 15. Bh4 {The bishop is too precious! The entire attack is based on the pinned knight.} Kg7 16. Qf3 Bd7 17. Rfe1 {Trading the rooks would definitely be a success for White.} Rxd5 18. Re4 {The rook is about to go to f4 with extreme pressure on the f6 knight.} Rf5 19. Qg3+ Kh6 20. Rae1 {The last piece joints the party, with a deadly effect. White may take on f6 and shift the rook to h4 . It's almost over.} *

