uch a foggy position will definitely enjoy the following lines. Maybe the force be with you!} 13. Rg1 Bf8 14. g4 Nh7 15. g5 Kh8 {Stockfish 15:} 16. Qh5 d6 17. Rg3 {This is engine's suggestion - the point is to cover h3 square to avoid Qd7 - h3 ideas trading the queens. Black is helpless anyway. If you're looking for simplicity, just take on h7 .} Bg7 18. gxh6 Be5 19. Rg7 {This is a final touch! The idea is to force Black to capture the rook, which would open the h file and access to the knight on h7 . White wins pretty much by force.} Bxg7 20. hxg7+ Kxg7 21. Qxh7+ Kf8 22. Qh6+ Ke7 23. Re1+ {Black's position is hopeless. It should end in a rather quick checkmate from this position. I'll leave the rest to you.} *

