uch a foggy position will definitely enjoy the following lines. Maybe the force be with you!} 13. Rg1 Bf8 14. g4 Nxd5 15. g5 {Obviously, White needs to proceed in the most forceful fashion. Once the g or h file is open, it should all be over. The engine claims it's "only" a big advantage for White. This generally means that Black still has defensive resources, which should not be underestimated. On the other hand, it's much easier to attack than to defend. Let's see how the game may proceed. Please keep in mind that all of this is original analysis, which never occurred in a game (at least not that I'm aware of).} Kh8 16. Qd4+ Bg7 17. Qxd5 d6 18. Rg3 {The material is equal but White maintains the attacking chances due to Black's exposed king. The White king may even quietly hide on h1 leaving the g1 square for the a1 rook.} *

