uch a foggy position will definitely enjoy the following lines. Maybe the force be with you!} 13. Rg1 Bf8 14. g4 d6 15. g5 Ng4 {Since Black has a material advantage, it makes sense to give back some of it in order to deprive White of the powerful rook. Let me show you how White can approach this.} 16. Rxg4 Bxg4 17. Qxg4 {Despite the material deficit, White still has the attack and fully dominates light squares thanks to this mighty bishop. It will probably not come as a surprise if I tell you that h7 and f7 are our new targets. The easiest follow-up is Qf5 . Ideally, we would like to have the rook on g1 but Kg2 , Rg1 , Kh1 might not be fast enough.} hxg5 18. Bh7+ {Wait, what?} Kxh7 {Taking the bishop allows White to win the queen by force. Not taking means Qh5 and Nxg5 will come with a devastating effect.} 19. Nxg5+ Kg8 20. Ne6+ Kh7 21. Nxd8 {White collects the queen anyway with an advantage.} *

