 push g4 - g5 completely opening the crucial g file. Next, the rook will come to g1 and I already feel bad for Black.} Rh8 {Clearly the strongest move for Black. It's necessary to protect the h6 pawn as well as cover the h7 square. However, finding the following continuation is in my opinion very difficult for Black. It involves a temporary queen sacrifice!} 15. g5 hxg5 16. Qxg5+ Kf8 17. Rg1 {White threatens Qg7 with a pratically finishing attack. The a1 rook will join the party in a moment by going to e1 .} Rg8 18. Qh6+ Ke8 19. Re1+ Be7 20. Qxf6 {The engine already indicates that White is winning by force in 13 moves! No-one is expecting you to find that in advance but this just shows how bad Black's position is. After the exchange of the rooks you will probably be looking at moves like Ng5 or Qh8 followed by Ne5 . Be creative!} *

