1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nd5 Be7 {A very logical move. Black focuses on quick development. The bishop's position is perhaps not impressive, but it does prevent Bg5 ideas.} 6. Bc4 {Other moves are certainly possible but this one appeals to me the most. What's more, Black is tempted to take the pawn on e4 , which leads to some spicy chess. A perfectly logical alternative for Black. It's a very a human reaction to run away from the centre, especially if one is surprised with the Belgrade Gambit!} O-O 7. O-O Nxe4 8. Re1 {It's just a matter of move order - transposition to 6... Nxe4 .} *

