1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nd5 Be7 {A very logical move. Black focuses on quick development. The bishop's position is perhaps not impressive, but it does prevent Bg5 ideas.} 6. Bc4 {Other moves are certainly possible but this one appeals to me the most. What's more, Black is tempted to take the pawn on e4 , which leads to some spicy chess. A perfectly logical alternative for Black. It's a very a human reaction to run away from the centre, especially if one is surprised with the Belgrade Gambit!} O-O 7. O-O Nxd5 8. exd5 {An important move, White voluntarily restricts the bishop by recapturing with the pawn. On the other hand, the black knight has to move somewhere and it's not clear where it should go. On top of that, the d4 pawn will not be protected anymore. Whether we should capture it or not, it's a different story.} Na5 9. Bd3 {In order to understand Black's main problem, it's worth looking at what would happen if White could make another move.} (9. Z0 {b4} Bb4 {Bxh7+ the classic bishop sacrifice is available and White has a finishing attack. Kxh7} 10. Ng5 {Kg8 Qh5+- Black will soon get checkmated or lose the queen.}) 9... c5 {Long story short: Black should not allow b2 - b4 as this deflects the bishop from e7 . In turn, the bishop on e7 prevents Bxh7 ideas as it covers the critical g5 square.} 10. d6 {You've seen this move before. The purpose is twofold: lure the bishop into taking on d6 to enable Bxh7 sacrifice and freeze the d7 pawn.} Bxd6 {We all know where this is going by now.} 11. Bxh7+ Kxh7 12. Ng5+ Kg6 13. h4 f5 14. h5+ ({In a recent online game, I forgot my analysis and opted for a different line.} 14. Qf3 Rh8 15. g4 f4 {In the game I actually had a mouse slip and took on f4 with the queen. The intended Qe4 finishes on spot.} 16. Qe4+ ({(} 16. Qxf4 Bxf4 {Normal 0-1 AttackingBeast (2751)-gmmitkov (2620) lichess.org 2022)}) ({( Kh6} 16. Nf7 {)}) 16... Kf6 17. Qf5+ Ke7 18. Qf7#) 14... Kf6 15. Qf3 {Black is up a piece but the exposed king is the more important factor. White has numerous attacking ideas: Qd5 , Re1 , Ne4 , Nh7 and g4 .} *

