e efficiently so that one of our minor pieces could go there.} h6 13. Ng5 {Yet another insane piece sacrifice. Such ideas normally work with the rook on h1 instead of f1 . Thanks to Black's bad piece coordination and rather slow development on queenside, this idea may actually work.} b6 {This is not critical but nicely illustrates White's attacking resources.} 14. Nh7 Re8 15. Qg4 Kh8 16. Ng5 {Back and forth. Once more, the knight is poisoned as opening the h file will seal the deal.} Rf8 17. Qe4 {Forking the h7 square and the rook on a8 .} g6 18. Nxf7+ Rxf7 19. Qxa8 {White's advantage is beyond dispute. However, White should quickly mobilize his pieces, i.e., the bishop on c1 and the rook on a1 to avoid any discussion.} *

