e efficiently so that one of our minor pieces could go there.} Bxh4 13. g4 {Astonishing idea! White has 2 main concepts here: one is to trap the bishop by g4 - g5 and the other one is to play Kg2 followed by Rh1 .} h6 14. g5 Bxg5 15. Nxg5 hxg5 16. Qh5 f5 17. Bxg5 Qe8 18. Qh4 {White maintains a powerful attack. The engine suggests proceeding with f2 - f3 and Kf2 in order to place the rooks on h1 and g1 . Remarkable!} *

