1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nd5 Be7 {A very logical move. Black focuses on quick development. The bishop's position is perhaps not impressive, but it does prevent Bg5 ideas.} 6. Bc4 {Other moves are certainly possible but this one appeals to me the most. What's more, Black is tempted to take the pawn on e4 , which leads to some spicy chess.} Nxe4 7. O-O {For a split second Black has coordination issues. The knight on e4 as well as the king on e8 mean a chance for creating tactical motifs along the e file. Black needs to castle as quickly as possible and retreat the knight. In the meantime, White will attempt to develop a powerful initative.} Nd6 {This seemingly normal move allows a nice tactical trick.} 8. Bf4 O-O 9. Re1 {Once more, the bishop is untouchable. If the knight is frozen on d6 , it means that the development of the bishop from c8 will be problematic.} Nxc4 10. Bxc7 Qe8 11. Nxd4 {It turns out that the threat of Nxc6 followed by capturing on e7 is devastating. In turn, taking on d4 allows the Nxe7 / Rxe7 intermezzo. I faced this move once in an online game. The following line is rather predictable.} d6 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. Nxe7+ Kh8 14. Ng6+ fxg6 15. Rxe8 Rxe8 16. Qd4 Ba6 17. b3 c5 18. Qd5 Nb6 19. Qxd6 {With a winning attack in a blitz game 1-0 (46) AttackingBeast (2715) -Nechto37 (2551) lichess.org 2022} *

