1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Nd5 Be7 {A very logical move. Black focuses on quick development. The bishop's position is perhaps not impressive, but it does prevent Bg5 ideas.} 6. Bc4 {Other moves are certainly possible but this one appeals to me the most. What's more, Black is tempted to take the pawn on e4 , which leads to some spicy chess.} Nxe4 7. O-O {For a split second Black has coordination issues. The knight on e4 as well as the king on e8 mean a chance for creating tactical motifs along the e file. Black needs to castle as quickly as possible and retreat the knight. In the meantime, White will attempt to develop a powerful initative.} O-O 8. Re1 {Simple and strong, White needs to put immediate pressure on the e file.} Nc5 {White has a few really attractive continuations.} 9. Rxe7 {In a practical game, this may easily be winning. It's possible to hold but it will require surgical precision.} Nxe7 {This natural recapture allows White to create mayhem.} 10. Bg5 {The pin itself is already a huge problem and it's not even the beginning.} Re8 11. Ne5 {Black is completely dominated as f7 and e7 are really fragile. Tactical motifs should be available in a moment.} Nxd5 12. Nxf7 {White wins a queen and keeps the attack.} *

