 Black has severe development problems.} Rg7 16. Nf5 Rg5 17. Qh6 {White threatens Nxf6 . It should definitely be allowed by Black.} Rxf5 18. Qg6+ Kf8 19. Qxf5 {White is 'only' down a piece, but the attack is on. The f6 pawn is about to fall which would be a sign of huge problems for Black. If needed, you will always have ideas like Re4 - g4 / h4 or Bd3 .} *

